records.addlTxt:
Defendant Jeremy Keith Zanders Jr appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Michael L. Chernin appeared by video for Jeremy Keith Zanders Jr.  Attorney John J Rejowski appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. 

HELD OFF THE RECORD VIA ZOOM. BRANCH 46 IS IN JURY TRIAL ON ANOTHER MATTER AND NOT AVAILABLE FOR TODAY'S HEARING. 
Case in Court for Scheduling Conference with Co-Defendant Case, 22CF3067. Defense received discovery material; however, has NOT received an offer from the State. Court addressed Defendant's other two cases, 21CF5302 and 21CF5273, pending in Branch 46. Case adjourned for Status hearing, Branch 46. Status hearing scheduled for December 6, 2022 at 08:30 am. Hearing will be held via Zoom Video Conference.

Defendant Jeremy Keith Zanders in court with attorney Michael L. Chernin.  Defendant Jeremy Keith Zanders in custody.  John J Rejowski appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  Jeremy Keith Zanders appeared by video means with Attorney.  
State's Witness was present. Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing. Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Court found probable cause and bound Defendant over for trial. 
State filed original Information. Defense counsel waived reading of Information, and entered a plea of Not Guilty on behalf of Defendant. Court ordered case adjourned for Scheduling Conference in Branch 46.  Scheduling conference scheduled for October 27, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Adjustment Number: 22A 076936,
Payable Number: 1025455,
Receipt Number: 22RP032281,
Amount: $20.00
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Co Def Deonta Span.

Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for Level 5 Supervision with Electronic Monitoring. 24 hour curfew. If electronic monitoring device is unavailable and cash bail has been paid, bail to revert to $75,000.  If Alternative bail is paid, Defendant to be released and placed on Electronic Monitoring waiting list. Court orders keep separate from co defendant with in custody.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Jeremy Keith Zanders in court with attorney Joel Alan Mogren.  Defendant Jeremy Keith Zanders in custody.  Karine O'Byrne appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Jeremy Keith Zanders appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Feiss, Branch 46. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for August 11, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
